    UnitedHealthcare® Options PPO

    Beginning January 1, 2021, SelectHealth members may have access to the UnitedHealthcare® Options PPO network.

    Before searching this network, make sure your plan includes in-network benefits through the UnitedHealthcare Options PPO when outside of Utah, Idaho, and Nevada. If your plan includes this network, your ID card will either have the logo on the front or include the language “plus out-of-network access.”

    If your ID card does not have either the logo or this language on the front, you only have access to this network for emergencies when traveling outside Utah, Idaho, and Nevada.

    When searching this network, it may populate providers in Utah, Idaho, and Nevada. However, SelectHealth members do not have in-network access to providers on UnitedHealthcare Options PPO in these three states. Members should use the appropriate local SelectHealth network in these states. . Those networks are listed on the back of your ID card.

    Questions? Call Member Services at 800-538-5038.

    To search for United Healthcare Options PPO providers, you'll be directed to a different website.
